review_blob: A delicious dark ale, albeit a tinge too sweet, even for this sweettooth.  Dark fruit and vanilla.  Love the bottle.

beer_brewer_name: Cervecera del sur del Peru (Backus & Johnston - SABMiller)
review_blob: This was the only drinkable beer in peru, and is much better(read not overly sweet) on tap.  Their lighter style pils is too much like a budweiser.
Looks and tastes like a much better corona.  Delicious with fish.  I would not buy it for myself though.
The first local brewery we tried moving here.  Cant say its top notch.  I wouldnt buy it again.
Im not entirely sure why we disliked this beer.  Perhaps were not into beers that are malted sweet.  I want to try it again,m to make sure my opinion wasnt skewed by chriss hate of sweeter beers.
I had this at a beer festival near their brewery in maine.  It was the top beer that we had at the festival by far.  A little too sweet on the molasses however.
Pretty intense and delicious beer.  Ima fan of most of sam smiths offerings, and was surprised at the last of 4+ ratings.

This beer is a highly carbonated, highly unique anf delicious brew.  I consider it my summer favorite, which can be bad since it is so high in alcohol (i believe 9 percent).  Notes of caramel, citrus and a nose of yeasty goodness.
Let me first say I dislike port wine so that could be the reason I rated this beer so low.  It tasted a bit like a malt beverage.
This is such a refreshing beer, light and crisp with notes of ripened bananas and citrus.  I bet it would pair well with a white fleshed fish.
I really think this tastes worse than budweiser.  Even with the orange slice, it comes off as watered-down, an d is not at all refreshing.  I shall not be wasting money on this again.
